Name: Engine Nymph
Title: God-Charged Engine
Requirements: 3 @Hull or less
Effects: When you are about to move the Argo, move the Argo two times instead. Do not resolve any other Voyage steps on the first tile moved to. If the tile you ignored was unexplored, place the Engine Nymph token on it. Next time you enter that tile, discard that token and treat the tile as if you have just revealed it

Name: Solitude Nymph
Title: Gaia's Hold
Requirements: At least 1 Titan has died or drawn an Obol
Effects: Immediately discard the drawn AI card, without resolving it. Treat it as resolved

Name: Amalthean Nymph
Title: Amalthea's Milk
Requirements: At least 1 Titan has died or drawn an Obol. When a Titan is about to die from an Obol Draw
Effects: Treat the Titan as if they drew a _You Live!_ Obol card. Additionally, they lose -3 @Danger and -3 @Fate

Name: Labyrinth Nymph
Title: Minotaur Logic
Requirements: At least 1 Titan has died or drawn an Obol. When a Titan is about to die from an Obol Draw
Effects: Immediately remove, move, or place 3 different Labyrinth tiles anywhere on the Board. All moved or placed tiles must create a connected Labyrinth path. The first Titan Attack this Round performed from a Labyrinth tile gains +1 @Power

Name: Depths Nymph
Title: Midnight Tide
Requirements: Any Titan has at least 4 Ambrosia tokens. Gain +6 @Fate as a group
Effects: Immediately remove all Terrain tiles with the Ambrosia keyword and discard all Ambrosia tokens from all Titans

Name: Sweets Nymph
Title: Grand Fete
Requirements: Be on a @City tile. You cannot use Voyage Technology abilities this day
Effects: Lower @ArgoFate to 0

Name: Nietzschean Nymph
Title: Transcend!
Requirements: A Titan has just died
Effects: Choose a Titan other than the one that just died. That Titan immediately Awakens, then discards 1 @Trespass token

Name: Forge Nymph
Title: Masterpiece
Requirements: None
Effects: Resolve the _Forging a Masterpiece_ Special Event of your current Cycle Storybook (or Cycle II Storybook for Cycle I). Give the acquired @Gear card to one of the Argonauts, that @Gear card gains the {Argonaut Possession} keyword. After the next Battle: Lose that @Gear card permanently. The Argonaut gains the [Apathy|CF1261] Fated Mnemos card

Name: Blade Nymph
Title: Vorpal Secret
Requirements: At least 1 Titan has died or drawn an Obol
Effects: Assign this card and the Blade Nymph token to a Titan. As long as you have this card, you have +1 @Power. Before each Power Roll you must say if you will Wound the Primordial or not. If you waver, discard this card and your Weapon. If you're sure and then you do not Wound, discard this card, permanently lose your Weapon, and draw an Obol. <Start of your turn:> Discard the Blade Nymph token. If you cannot, discard this card instead

Name: Knowledge Nymph
Title: Page Infinite
Requirements: Be on a @City tile. You cannot use Voyage Technology abilities this day
Effects: Immediately research 1 @CombatTech or @StructuralTech Technology. You need to meet the Technology card's requirements

Name: Mask Nymph
Title: Face, Off
Requirements: Start of Battle
Effects: One Titan may perform their turn before the first Primordial Round, instead of in the first Titan Round

Name: Curiosity Nymph
Title: Insatiable Secret
Requirements: @ArgoFate 6+
Effects: This Nymph does not exhaust. Immediately gain +1 @Progress or +1 @ArgoKnowledge. Gain +1 unavoidable @Doom

Name: Night Nymph
Title: Veil of Nyx
Requirements: None
Effects: Choose a waterway on any explored Map tile, leading to an unexplored tile. Reveal that tile and place the Night Nymph token on it. When you enter that tile, discard the token. Treat that tile as if you've just revealed it

Name: Age Nymph
Title: Aeon Bypass
Requirements: At least 1 Titan has died
Effects: Choose a Titan. During the Titan Round, the chosen Titan gains a bonus turn. OR When a Titan dies, place the Age Nymph token on their space or the closest legal free space. During the next Titan Round, the chosen Titan may discard the Age Nymph token to reappear in its space and take their turn. At the end of that Titan Round, the Titan disappears again

Name: Hope Nymph
Title: Stuff of Legends
Requirements: There is only 1 Titan alive
Effects: Until the end of Battle, the last Titan can perform an additional @MovementAction and @CombatAction. They cannot suffer {Knockdown} or {Time-clocked} and cannot gain @Rage over 9. When they resolve an Obol Draw, they always draw from the standard 2-card Obol deck

Name: Machina Nymph
Title: Postmodern Exorcism
Requirements: At least 1 Titan has died
Effects: Unexhaust all @Gear of all Titans. Each prepared Argo Ability regains 1 @Energy token

Name: Silica Nymph
Title: Atomic Thaw
Requirements: At least 1 Titan has died or drawn an Obol
Effects: Immediately create 6 Glass [Irem Tower|DI2028] tiles. A Glass Irem Tower loses the {Shifting} keyword and gains the {Destructible} keyword

Name: Midas Nymph
Title: The Double-Edged Coin
Requirements: At least 1 Titan has died or you have 16+ Midas tokens among all your Titans
Effects: Immediately remove all Midas tokens and Conditon cards from all Titans. OR Immediately turn all Ambrosia tokens into Midas tokens

Name: Natron Nymph
Title: Memory of an Ancient Shore
Requirements: When an Argonaut is about to die and either *During Battle:* At least 1 Titan has died. *During Voyage:* @Crew 3 or less.
Effects: Prevent the Argonaut death, as if you used an Echo of Recollection, and lose -1 Titan instead

Name: Ambrosia Nymph
Title: Final Descent
Requirements: At least 1 Titan has died or drawn an Obol
Effects: Discard all Ambrosia tokens from all Titans. Each Titan gains 1 Aether token for each 2 Ambrosia tokens discarded this way

Name: Aether Nymph
Title: Oxygen Destroyer
Requirements: At least 1 Titan has died or drawn an Obol
Effects: Flip all Aether tokens or all Oxygen tokens
